<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena nitida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from Morocco by 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="3 - 54" refId="B50" refString="Warncke, K, 1974. Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 50: 3 - 54" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena)." volume="50" year="1974">Warncke (1974)</bibRefCitation>
under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena nitida subsp. mixtura" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitida" subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena nitida mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1967. This subspecies was described from Portugal and Spain under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena limata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena limata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Smith, 1853 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="mixtura" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Warncke, 1967). However, Warncke transferred this subspecies into combination with 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="3 - 54" refId="B50" refString="Warncke, K, 1974. Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 50: 3 - 54" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena)." volume="50" year="1974">Warncke 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Eos" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="119 - 223" refId="B53" refString="Warncke, K, 1976. Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil B. Eos 50: 119 - 223" title="Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil B." volume="50" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
) without any apparent justification. Examination of the type series of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. n. subsp. mixtura" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="n." subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. n. mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows that its original placement was justified based on its bivoltine behaviour and the darker colouration of its tergal and scopal hairs (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" author="Wood, TJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="201 - 228" refId="B61" refString="Wood, TJ, Cross, I, Baldock, DW, 2020a. Updates to the bee fauna of Portugal with the description of three new Iberian Andrena species (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Zootaxa 4790: 201 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" title="Updates to the bee fauna of Portugal with the description of three new Iberian Andrena species (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" volume="4790" year="2020 a">Wood et al. 2020a</bibRefCitation>
), and that therefore records of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. n. subsp. mixtura" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="n." subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. n. mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from North Africa (none of which are part of the type series) refer to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. limata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="limata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. limata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be removed from the Moroccan list.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
